# Digital Clock

This is a simple digital clock application created using Python and Tkinter.

## Features

- Displays the current time, date, and day.
- Updates the time every second.

## Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed:

- Python 3.x
- Tkinter library
- PIL (Python Imaging Library) library

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```shell
   git clone https://github.com/rohitnitr/digital-clock-python.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```shell
   cd digital-clock-python
   ```

3. Install the required dependencies:

   ```shell
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

## Usage

Run the following command to start the digital clock application:

```shell
python digital_clock.py
```

The clock will be displayed on your screen.

